# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Warehouse repo .gitignore
#
# Principle: only commit the SOURCE of the pipeline (notebooks, lib/, scripts,
# seeds, overrides, docs). Everything else is regenerable from upstream APIs
# and lives on disk between runs (locally or in the GHA Actions cache).
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── ephemeral data ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Raw upstream API caches — 800MB+ and growing. Restored from GHA cache between
# runs; never in git.
data/raw/

# Pipeline outputs (parquets + CSVs + emitted JSON). Regenerable from data/raw/
# via refresh.py. The PWA gets these via the GHA workflow pushing JSONs to the
# PWA repo, not via this repo.
data/processed/

# Event-state files for the per-tick "what's newly finished" gating. Restored
# from GHA cache between runs.
data/.event_state.json
data/.last_daily_run

# ── python / jupyter byproducts ──────────────────────────────────────────────
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
.ipynb_checkpoints/
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/

# ── virtualenvs / IDE ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.venv/
venv/
.env
.env.local
.vscode/
.idea/
.DS_Store

# ── notebook execution outputs ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# refresh.py re-executes notebooks in place and writes outputs back. We DON'T
# commit those (they'd be massive churn on every run); strip with nbstripout
# locally before committing notebook edits. The GHA runner doesn't commit
# notebooks back at all — only pushes JSON to the PWA repo.
# (Notebooks themselves are tracked; this is just a reminder.)
